      ],
      "last_updated": "2026-04-28",
      "status": "scaffold",
      "_note_2026_04_28": "InferenceRouter skeleton per ADR 004 §'Buildable today': rule-based classifier (chat|tool|code), profile-driven slot lookup, DispatchDecision audit trail. Wired into routers/chat.py: chat handler routes via _route_request() then constructs LLM via _llm_from_decision(); _handle_message emits decision.to_audit_dict() in WS done event for runtime UI consumption. Behavior preservation: legacy single-model installs short-circuit via _resolve_local_override (user-picked model → identity dispatch). Profile-driven path activates when no model override is set. Code-review hardening rounds 1+2 (2026-04-28): _get_llm cache keyed on routed (provider,model,base_url) from the DispatchDecision rather than user input — keeps cache and audit consistent once profile-driven multi-slot installs ship; privacy gate centralised inside _route_request so every entry point (chat handler, duel handler, _make_llm test shim) gets it consistently and only once per call; InferenceRouter.dispatch() is intentionally privacy-naive with the boundary documented at the module docstring level so future non-chat callers know they own the privacy assertion; duel handler also routes through _route_request so it shares the cache and audit shape with chat turns; chat handler passes tools=None to classify (TOOLS is always-populated in this codebase, would dominate every request as 'tool' otherwise; classifier 'tool' branch preserved as the seam ADR 004 enumerates for future explicit-tools call sites); type hints (\"DispatchDecision\") added on _get_llm/_llm_from_decision via TYPE_CHECKING import. Deferred per ADR 004 §'Blocked by upstream ADRs': downgrade-ladder walking under memory pressure (needs production-grade Apple Silicon signals, ADR 003), pinned_loadout enforcement (ADR 008), ML classifier upgrade."
    },
    "profiles": {
      "doc": "docs/features/profiles.md",
      "type": "feature",
      "sources": [
        "backend/services/profile_service.py",
        "backend/services/_config_io.py",
