      ],
      "depends_on": [],
      "last_updated": "2026-04-28",
      "status": "scaffold",
      "_note_2026_04_28": "ProfilePack schema + initial 3-profile scaffold per ADR 005: generic-knowledge-worker (default), developer-devops (coder ladder), patent-prosecutor (no coder, vision required). Schema lands now; remaining 6 profiles in ADR 005's catalog table deferred until domain validation per ADR 005 §'Open follow-ups' #1. get_active_profile() reads app/config.json:active_profile_id with fallback to DEFAULT_PROFILE_ID. Embedding/TTS slot specs are name-only placeholders pending the embedding+TTS slot consumers. Tauri-side profile picker / change UX deferred to post-ADR-003. Code-review hardening rounds 1+2 (2026-04-28): mtime-cached get_active_profile (router's hot path no longer re-reads config every WS message); set_active_profile / set_active_local_model / clear_active_local_model all routed through services/_config_io.py:locked_config_update which (a) takes a POSIX fcntl.flock so concurrent writers can't lose each other's updates via read-modify-write race, (b) writes via atomic_write_json (temp-file + fsync + os.replace + parent-dir fsync, atomic against process crash and best-effort against power loss), (c) skips on unchanged so no-op writes don't bump mtime and invalidate the cache. context_perf_mode_default is Literal-typed so typos fail at construction. validate_profile_catalog() catches model_id typos at CI time; _walk_slot_specs has a schema-drift introspection test (TestWalkSlotSpecs) that asserts ProfileStack.model_fields matches the walker — adding a new optional slot without updating _walk_slot_specs fails CI. KNOWN_PLACEHOLDER_MODEL_IDS is the explicit allowlist for intentional placeholders. Multi-worker note: cache is process-local; uvicorn --workers N has eventual consistency across workers — single-worker desktop binary per ADR 003 makes this moot today."
    },
